summaries.short: Season 2 Premiere. Ben and Cam plan a CRISP pop-up event; Rachel still holds a flame for Ben; Rene has a new billboard.
summaries.full: Season 2 Premiere. Ben and Cam return from a successful trip to Tokyo full of optimism--and with duffle bags of hoodies for a CRISP pop-up store event. Back from her soul-searching globe-trot, Rachel realizes she still has feelings for Ben. Rene puts up a head-turning Rasta Monsta billboard that incenses his girlfriend; Domingo expands his business beyond dog-walking.

summaries.short: Ben and Cam are stuck between two sales reps and a hard place; Rene leans on a client; Rachel lights up with Domingo.
summaries.full: Ben and Cam are stuck between their new sales rep and a hard place when they have the opportunity to crash a brunch hosted by the well-connected Nancy Frankenburg. Meanwhile, Cam is determined to move out of his grandmother's place; Ben makes an indifferent step toward commitment; Rene leans on an indebted client; and Rachel lands a new job and lights up with Domingo.

summaries.short: In the Season One finale, Cam suspects Rene in the disappearance of his and Ben's tees; Rachel makes a life choice.
summaries.full: In the Season One finale, Cam suspects Rene of having something to do with the theft of the Rasta Monsta truck filled with his and Ben's Crisp tees--but is he man enough to confront his hot-tempered cousin? Meanwhile, Rachel makes a decision that impacts the lives of Ben, Edie and Darren.

summaries.short: CRISP lands a promising but unpaid gig; Rachel gives Ben a gift; Cam raises money for a river-view apartment; Rene shoots a viral video.
summaries.full: Fashion rep Nancy lands CRISP a promising but unpaid gig. Rachel bestows a lavish gift on Ben after learning that he and Julie may be parting ways. Cam goes into the dealing business with Domingo to help raise money for a river-view apartment. Rene shoots a Rasta Monsta viral video with Wilfredo Gomez, and gets closer to his girlfriend Debbie.

summaries.short: While Ben is getting tight with Julie, Rachel is put off by Darren's offer; Rene's big meeting with John Lardner gets an unexpected guest.
summaries.full: While Ben is getting tight with Julie, Rachel is put off by Darren's sudden offer to let her and Edie design a hotel. Meanwhile, Cam and Ben agree to hand out Rasta Monsta samples at Union Square; Rene agrees to meet with John Lardner, the Jamaica-based owner of Rasta Monsta, about taking over North American distribution rights to the drink.

summaries.short: Ben and Rachel's platonic friendship is tested; Cam scores a plum location for a CRISP photo shoot; Rene collects on a debt.
summaries.full: Ben's platonic friendship with Rachel is tested. Meanwhile, Kapo stresses about speaking from the heart in his best-man speech; Cam charms Lulu's dad to secure the perfect location (and an unlikely model) for CRISP's new 'lookbook' photo shoot; Rene seeks to collect on a debt to cover the costs of Rasta Monsta's expanding business (and to buy bling for Debbie).

summaries.short: Ben and Cam find it hard to meet Hidemi's vintage-tee quota of 300 until an attractive retail employee named Julie helps bail them out.
summaries.full: Ben and Cam find it hard to meet Hidemi's vintage-tee quota of 300--until an attractive retail employee named Julie helps bail them out. Rene gets some fatherly advice on how to handle an impending schoolyard showdown. Rachel's trip to Connecticut to check on a behind-schedule carpenter ends with Darren taking her to meet his mother--and asking a big question.
